\begin{tabular}{l} srs-ResourceldList, srs-PosResourceldList The IDs of the SRS-Resources/SRS-PosResource used in this SRS-ResourceSet/SRS-PosResourceSet. If this SRS-ResourceSet is configured with usage set to codebook, the srs-ResourceldList contains at most 2 entries. If this SRS-ResourceSet is configured with usage set to nonCodebook, the srs-ResourceldList contains at most 4 entries. \end{tabular} \begin{tabular}{l} srs-ResourceSetid, srs-PosResourceSetid The ID of this resource set. It is unique in the context of the BWP in which the parent SRS-Config is defined. \end{tabular}
